{"title":"New $99 Lazer Cerro Helmet is Gravel Focused with Road Benefits","link":"https://bikerumor.com/affordable-lazer-cerro-helmet-gravel-road/","date":1686836183000,"content":"<p>Gravel is in vogue, but lots of the products arriving with gravel in the name feature some excellent non-gravel specific benefits as well. The new Lazer Cerro KinetiCore helmet offers the best of the road and off-road worlds — dovetailing with gravel.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-visor-.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-visor--800x534.jpeg\" alt=\"Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-visor\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-visor--800x534.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-visor--297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-visor--120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-visor--768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-visor--720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-visor-.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The design has a road-focused appearance from head-on, but a tiny visor is visible as the view comes to the side. The Lazer Cerro has many add-ons that make it more versatile than most, especially paired with the $99 price tag.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-dial-.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-dial--800x534.jpeg\" alt=\"Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-dial-\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-dial--800x534.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-dial--297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-dial--120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-dial--768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-dial--720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-dial-.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Lazer Cerro KinetiCore has built-in eyewear docking slots to keep glasses in place on bumpy roads. And if you get too gnarly on said roads — KinetiCore technology should protect you against direct and rotational impact.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/lazer-Coyote-KinetiCore-helmet-review7-Large-rotated.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/lazer-Coyote-KinetiCore-helmet-review7-Large-800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Lazer Coyote Kineticore helmet\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/lazer-Coyote-KinetiCore-helmet-review7-Large-800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/lazer-Coyote-KinetiCore-helmet-review7-Large-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/lazer-Coyote-KinetiCore-helmet-review7-Large-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/lazer-Coyote-KinetiCore-helmet-review7-Large-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/lazer-Coyote-KinetiCore-helmet-review7-Large-rotated.jpeg 1280w\" /></a><figcaption>Example of Lazer KinetiCore technology on the Lazer Coyote Kineticore helmet. Photo Zach Overholt</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>What’s KinetiCore Technology?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/lazer-kineticore-helmets/\" target=\"_blank\">Lazer’s KinetiCore technology</a> features built-in rotational-impact protection thanks to unique Controlled Crumple Zones incorporated into the internal structure of the helmet. KinetiCore also uses less overall material, adding improved ventilation, a lighter-weight helmet design, and fewer plastics used in construction (not to mention more friendly to long hair).</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-back-side-.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-back-side--800x534.jpeg\" alt=\"Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-back-side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-back-side--800x534.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-back-side--297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-back-side--120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-back-side--768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-back-side--720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-back-side-.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Magnetic Buckle</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Lazer adds a magnetic buckle to keep the Lazer Cerro KinetiCore on your head. Plus, along with a small visor, an insect net will protect riders from rain, gravel, mud, and many flying insects.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-setting-super-.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-setting-super--800x534.jpeg\" alt=\"Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-setting-super\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-setting-super--800x534.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-setting-super--297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-setting-super--120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-setting-super--768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-setting-super--720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Lazers-Cerro-Helmet-side-setting-super-.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Lazer Cerro KinetiCore Specs</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Available in three sizes (S / M / L)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Lightweight 270g M CE</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>MSRP: </strong>€99,99 / $99,99</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Available:</strong> Now</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://lazersport.us/\"><em>Lazersport.us</em></a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/affordable-lazer-cerro-helmet-gravel-road/\">New $99 Lazer Cerro Helmet is Gravel Focused with Road Benefits</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Jordan Villella","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"eb0738a31c7e4268aacf57e6ea10065beb0740a1713478edc547785b343bb605","category":"Cycling"}